<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Thatcher-Bush     05-11 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Thatcher-Bush,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kissinger Predicts Close Bush-Thatcher Relationship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher will have as
close or closer a political relationship with President Bush than
with his predecessor Ronald Reagan, Henry Kissinger predicted.
   The former U.S. secretary of state made the remarks Wednesday
night in an interview with Britain's Sky Television.
   Mrs. Thatcher, one of Reagan's closest allies during his
two-term presidency, is due to hold talks with Bush when he visits
Britain for two days starting May 31 during a European tour.
   Kissinger said: ``The relationship, good as it was between
President Reagan and Mrs. Thatcher, will be at least as good, if
not better, between President Bush and Prime Minister Thatcher.''
   ``Mr. Reagan based his relationships very much on personal
intuition. President Bush is a man who is more reflective about the
conceptual matters,'' Kissinger added.
</TEXT>
