<FIRST>r a PM-Panama-Carter     05-11 0212</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Panama-Carter,0220</SECOND>
<HEAD>Carter Tells of Panama Election Fraud</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Panama, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Jimmy Carter has videotaped a
program in Spanish to give Latins in the United States and in nine
Latin American countries his view that the election in Panama was
rigged.
   In the program taped Wednesday, Carter, who observed the
elections as part of a team that included former President Ford,
urged Panamamian leader Gen. Manuel Antonio Noriega to acknowledge
the fraud.
   ``I have personally witnessed these criminal acts,'' Carter said
on Cable News Network's Noticiero Telemundo news program.
   ``It is very important that the world and particularly the
leaders of Western democracies denounce these results and condemn
General Noriega.''
   Carter in 1978 signed the agreement with the late Gen. Omar
Torrijos under which Panama will take control of the Panama Canal
in 1999.
   The Electoral Tribunal in Panama annulled Sunday's presidential
election after paramilitary forces beat the opposition candidates
and attacked protesters who said the government had rigged the
balloting.
   Noticiero Telemundo is shown on 20 Spanish-language stations in
the United States and is distributed to nine Latin American
countries, said CNN spokesman Steve Haworth.
   Those countries in the past included Panama, but Haworth said
that country is not allowing CNN reports to be aired.
</TEXT>
