<HEAD>Ku Klux Klan Leader Deposed Because He Was Born a Jew</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 4th graf to CLARIFY that birthplace was Philadelphia, Pa.,
sted Miss.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The leader of Mississippi's Christian
Knights of the Ku Klux Klan has been deposed because he was born a
Jew, KKK officials said.
   ``I just felt it was best to get a new grand dragon for
Mississippi,'' said Virgil Griffin of Mount Holly, N.C., national
head of the Christian Knights of the KKK.
   The removal of Jordan Gollub ``mostly concerned his Jewish
background,'' Griffin said. Griffin would not discuss his views on
Jews, but Klan organizations have historically despised Jews,
blacks and Catholics.
   Gollub, born in Philadelphia, Pa., to Jewish parents and reared
in a suburb there, said Wednesday he now considers himself a
Christian. He lives in Poplarville.
   He said Griffin dislikes his background ``and the fact that I'm
against Catholics joining the Klan.''
   Gollub said he will form his own Klan organization.
   ``I find it ironic that the leader of the Klan was a Jew,
obviously a self-hating Jew,'' said Eric Gurvis, rabbi at Beth
Israel Congregation in Jackson.
   Gollub's removal as grand dragon ``points out the senseless
hatred that seems to be a part of the Klan. I can't say it's
unexpected.''
