<HEAD>Mine Found Off Bahrain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Bahrain navy boat disposed Thursday of
a floating mine off the coast near the gulf island's international
airport, the official Gulf News Agency reported.
   The mine was found in territorial waters east of Al-Muharraq,
where the airport is located, and detonated, the news agency said.
   Mines left over from the Iran-Iraq war continue to turn up along
the Arabian coast, nearly nine months after a cease-fire took hold
Aug. 20.
   The contact-type mines break loose from underwater moorings off
Iraq and drift southward, threatening commercial shipping and
fishing craft.
   Two weeks ago, authorities said an oil tanker moored off the
United Arab Emirates was damaged by a derelict mine.
