<HEAD>Dissident Writer Dead at 76</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dominik Tatarka, a dissident
writer and signer of the Charter 77 human rights document, has died
at the age of 76.
   The terse report in the Communist Party daily Rude Pravo did not
mention Tatarka's human rights activities or the ban on his
writings.
   In the last 20 years, his works were not published by the state,
although they were widely circulated in self-published editions.
