<SECOND>AM-Jewish Klan Leader,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ku Klux Klan Deposes State Leader Who Was Born a Jew</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A national Klan organization has replaced
its Mississippi leader because he was born a Jew.
   Jordan Gollub of Poplarville, deposed as leader of the
Mississippi Christian Knights of the Ku Klux Klan, said Wednesday
he will form his own Klan organization, either under the name of
Southern Knights of the Great Forest or Gulf KKK Inc.
   Gollub, born and reared in Philadelphia, Pa., by Jewish parents,
said he considers himself a Christian. He said national Klan leader
Virgil Griffin of Mount Holly, N.C., dislikes his ``background and
the fact that I'm against Catholics joining the Klan.''
   Griffin said Gollub's removal was ``mostly concerned (with) his
Jewish background.''
   The Klan historically has directed hate campaigns against Jews,
blacks and Catholics, but Gollub said Griffin's faction allows
Catholic members.
   ``I find it ironic that the leader of the Klan was a Jew,
obviously a self-hating Jew,'' said Eric Gurvis, rabbi at Beth
Israel Congregation in Jackson. Gurvis said Gollub's removal as
grand dragon ``points out the senseless hatred that seems to be a
part of the Klan. I can't say it's unexpected.''
   As head of the Christian Knights, Gollub has marched in several
towns, usually with no more than a couple dozen Klansmen. Griffin
would not reveal the name of his new grand dragon.
</TEXT>
