<HEAD>Two to Fill Sawyer Shoes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It took two correspondents to fill the shoes one
Diane Sawyer left at CBS' ``60 Minutes.''
   The network on Thursday announced that Meredith Vieira and Steve
Kroft are the new ``co-editors'' of the top 10-rated, 22-year-old
newsmagazine.
   Both come from the network's newer newsmagazine, ``West 57th.''
