   James said the congressman would be in the hospital about a week.
   Udall has had Parkinson's disease for more than 10 years.
   The disorder stems from deterioration of brain nerve centers
that control movement. The disease's effects can be controlled with
drugs that help restore chemical balance. Udall has undergone
treatment at NIH in the past.
