<FIRST>r a AM-People-SegalAwards     05-11 0179</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Segal Awards,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Sarafina!' And Met Soprano Honored</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The third annual Martin E. Segal Awards were
presented Thursday to 23 members of Broadway's ``Sarafina!'' and to
Andrea Gruber, a soprano in the Metropolitan Opera's young artists
development program.
   The award, given to young artists at the Lincoln Center for the
Performing Arts, was established in 1986 in honor of Segal, who
retired that year as chairman of Lincoln Center.
   The Lincoln Center Theater, which produced ``Sarafina!,'' will
receive $4,000 to distribute to the 23 cast members honored.
Gruber, 23, who will make her Metropolitan Opera debut in
``Gotterdammerung,'' was also awarded $4,000.
   Gruber also will sing with the Chicago Symphony, with the Royal
Scottish Opera as Leonora in ``La Forza del Destino'' and with the
Cologne Opera as Amelia in ``Simon Boccanegra.''
   The cast of ``Sarafina!'' consists of singers and dancers, ages
17 to 22. Two are American and 21 are from South Africa.
``Sarafina!'' opened at Lincoln Center in September 1987.
   The awards are to be used for further study and career
advancement.
