<FIRST>r a AM-Grumpy'sTravels     05-11 0354</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Grumpy's Travels,0367</SECOND>
<HEAD>Concrete Lawn Dwarf Back Home After Whirlwind Vacation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAUGERTIES, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Grumpy the lawn dwarf is home safe after
a five-week whirlwind tour of the country, but his owners have no
idea who treated the snarling statue to a vacation.
   Grumpy, a 20-inch, 80-pound concrete statue of the character in
the Walt Disney movie classic, ``Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs,''
disappeared from Carol and Gene Horne's porch March 16 while the
couple was out.
   ``When we came back, I couldn't set my finger on it, but I felt
something was missing,'' Carol Horne said. ``The next morning my
daughter said, `Mom, there's somebody missing.'''
   Bashful, Doc, Sneezy, Happy, Sleepy, Dopey and the 400-pound
Snow White were untouched. Grumpy was gone.
   On April 26, a freshly-scrubbed Grumpy returned. The sign
dangling from his shoulders said, ``I'm home.''
   An accompanying envelope contained 35 photographs from his
journey, many of them with captions on the back.
   Grumpy's travels included visits to Yankee Stadium, Colorado,
North and South Carolina, St. Louis and Texas.
   There were snapshots of Grumpy ogling bikini-clad women from a
Florida sand dune, Grumpy standing in front of the Lincoln Memorial
in Washington, D.C., Grumpy dining at a McDonald's restaurant.
   ``My husband and I, we were laughing so hard at these pictures,
my husband was late for work,'' Horne said.
   She said neither she nor the police know who took Grumpy. She
theorizes that ``it's someone with an engineering background. The
printing on the back of the pictures is very similar to the type
you see on blueprints.''
   Horne said Grumpy had vanished before, turning up once in front
of a local Dairy Queen and in the back seat of a restaurant
manager's car.
   ``She saw somebody looking over her shoulder and started
screaming. He was just standing there with his arms folded and that
snarl on his face,'' Horne said.
   But alas, all good things must end. Horne said she plans to have
all the dwarfs cemented in place.
   Nevertheless, she admits to envying Grumpy's wandering ways.
   ``He gets to go everywhere. I never get to go anywhere.''
</TEXT>
