<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
242,841 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
242,038, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 252,408 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 159,466 cars this week,
compared with 153,062 a week ago and 167,892 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 83,375,
compared with last week's 88,976 and last year's 84,516.
   Canadian automakers were to build 24,445 cars this week, up from
21,974 a week ago but down from last year's 27,168.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,427,
compared with 21,603 a week ago and 20,112 in the same week last
year.
