<FILEID>AP-NR-05-11-89 1309EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Retailers     05-11 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Retailers,0202</SECOND>
<HEAD>May Reports Increase in Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   May Department Stores Co. on Thursday reported
a slight increase in earnings for the first quarter, in which the
company opened 17 new stores.
   For the three months ended April 29 May reported earnings of $63
million, or 45 cents a share, on revenues of $2.6 billion, compared
with $62 million, or 41 cents a share, on revenues of $2.2 billion
for the first period last year.
   ``We are very pleased with our sales and earnings increases for
the first quarter and are encouraged by the good start for 1989,''
said David C. Farrell, chairman and chief executive of the St.
Louis-based retailer. ``We have a lot of important programs in
process and expect another successful year for May.''
   During the first quarter, the company opened two department
stores, one discount store and 14 Payless ShoeSource stores. The
company said that by the end of the year, it will have opened 11
department stores, four discount stores and 140 Payless stores,
part of a $3.7 billion five-year capital spending plan.
   May is one of the largest retailers in the United States, with
3,092 stores.
</TEXT>
