<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0262</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were higher in moderate afternoon
trading as concerns about inflation continued to dominate the
market.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 5.32 to 2,379.77
at 2 p.m. EDT. The blue-chip indicator was up 0.73 at noon EDT.
   Advancers outnumbered decliners by about a 6 to 5 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, with 697 issues up, 582 down and 601
unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 106.85 million shares.
   The market got an early lift from bond prices, which firmed in
response to a smaller-than-expected rise in retail sales. The
Commerce Department reported that retail sales rose a modest 0.4
percent in April
   However, the market remained focused on Friday's report on
producer prices, which investors hope will provide a better clue
about inflation and the economy's growth.
   Traders said equity investors also were keeping an eye on the
bond market where players are awaiting the outcome of the
Treasury's 30-year bond sale.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.41 to 171.54.
   At the American Exchange, the market value index had advanced
0.38 to 345.18.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, Avon was down } to
39[, Pan Am was off { to 4{ and Eastman Kodak had fallen | to 43.
   General Electric was up } to 48|, Block Enterprises had gained 2
to 28\ and Ford Motor was up ] 46}.
