<UNK>Eds: Members who used f0294, transmitted May 10 with a New York dateline,
are asked to use the following story:</UNK>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported erroneously on
Wednesday that in settlements of civil insider trading charges with
the Securities and Exchange Commission, Henry M. Porter, of
Buffalo, N.Y., agreed to relinquish more than $78,000 in alleged
illegal trading profits and William Wolski, of Marietta, Ga.,
agreed to relinquish more than $37,000 in alleged illegal profits.
   Wolski actually agreed to relinquish more than $78,000 and
Porter agreed to relinquish more than $37,000.
