<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   05-11 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Share Prices Fall</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with later activity, closing index;
No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed mostly lower on London's Stock
Exchange Thursday, in an atmosphere of continued unease about
possible labor actions.
   Despite a strong start, the market was unable to regain its
composure after several early selling waves, and prices spent most
of the day drifting in a narrow range.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished 6.4
points, or 0.3 percent, lower at 2,110.6. The index opened with a
gain of 1.3 points, but then quickly dropped to its lowest level,
showing a loss of 9.9 points.
   The market has been plagued in recent weeks by threatened
strikes in public transportation, power plants, broadcasting and
docks, raising fears of further upward pressure on inflation.
   Volume fell to 430.5 million shares from 466.6 million on
Wednesday.
   The Financial Times 30-share index was 4.7 points lower at
1,758.7 at the close. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 2.84
points to close at 1,196.92.
</TEXT>
