<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0247</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was higher in moderate
afternoon trading, influenced by higher bond prices and a firming
dollar.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 8.43 to 2,382.88
at 3 p.m. EDT. The blue-chip indicator was up 5.32 points an hour
earlier.
   Advancers outnumbered decliners by about 6 to 5 on the New York
Stock Exchange, with 740 issues up, 606 down and 570 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 124.25 million shares.
   Analysts said stocks had firmed in response to a strengthening
bond market following the end of the Treasury's three-day
borrowing. However, activity was restrained with many participants
on the sidelines.
   The market got an early lift from bond prices, which firmed in
response to a smaller-than-expected rise in retail sales. The
Commerce Department reported that retail sales rose a modest 0.4
percent in April
   Later, the market drifted lower on concern about Friday's
wholesale prices report, which investors hope will provide a better
clue about inflation and the economy's growth.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.57 to 171.70.
   At the American Exchange, the market value index had advanced
0.64 to 345.44.
